156
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:52,630
Otherwise, when you're abroad,

157
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,320
I can't come to pick you up.

158
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,030
Got it.

159
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:58,600
I forget when I'm busy.

160
00:08:58,630 --> 00:09:00,000
Let me use the computer for a bit.

161
00:09:07,620 --> 00:09:11,580
(Yuan Xia's weather forecast app:
Exclusive weather forecasts by Wei Ziqi)

162
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,270
What are these?

163
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,000
Check your phone.

164
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:21,790
Look.

165
00:09:24,390 --> 00:09:26,270
Dear Yuan Yuan, good evening.

166
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:28,670
Here's the weather forecast
for tomorrow.

167
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,200
The highest temperature

168
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,790
will be 28 to 30 degrees Celsius,

169
00:09:31,910 --> 00:09:33,750
locally 29 to 32 degrees Celsius,

170
00:09:34,020 --> 00:09:35,540
with thunderstorms in the afternoon.

171
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:37,280
Remember to bring an umbrella
when you go out.

172
00:09:38,910 --> 00:09:40,820
This way, you won't forget
to bring an umbrella

173
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,390
even when you're busy.

174
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,030
Ni Ning.

175
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,600
I'm serious.

176
00:10:13,790 --> 00:10:16,240
I need you to talk to me
about this matter

177
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:17,720
with a serious attitude.

178
00:10:17,790 --> 00:10:18,870
You can drive,

179
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:20,960
but when you need to accelerate,
you accelerate,

180
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,510
and when you need to brake, you brake.

181
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:24,440
You can't just change lanes randomly.

182
00:10:24,550 --> 00:10:26,720
You need to follow traffic rules,

183
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:27,440
understand?

184
00:10:28,030 --> 00:10:28,840
Okay.

185
00:10:30,790 --> 00:10:31,840
When did you arrive?

186
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,000
I heard everything.

187
00:10:35,250 --> 00:10:37,320
I just wanted to have
a formal conversation with you.

188
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:38,080
Sure, we can talk.

189
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:40,600
I'll decide the place to talk.

190
00:10:44,380 --> 00:10:49,300
(Shady Book House: Because of you,
this city holds memories.)

191
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,440
I didn't expect

192
00:10:56,670 --> 00:10:58,240
that our date before I went abroad

193
00:10:58,440 --> 00:10:59,670
would be at a bookstore.

194
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,510
I'm here to help you study,

195
00:11:01,670 --> 00:11:03,790
so you'll adapt better
when you get there.

196
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:11,440
Look at that, what's that?

197
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,390
Hello,

198
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,240
I want to ask, what is that?

199
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:20,270
This is a time-travel postcard.

200
00:11:20,270 --> 00:11:20,960
If you have

201
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:23,000
something you want to say

202
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,200
to each other or to yourself,

203
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:27,480
you can go into our phone booth,

204
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,240
make a call,

205
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:30,080
and you'll get a postcard.

206
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:32,390
The postcard has a QR code.

207
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:33,870
We'll send it out in a year.

208
00:11:33,870 --> 00:11:36,600
When the recipient scans the QR code,

209
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:39,390
they can hear what you said today.

210
00:11:40,030 --> 00:11:40,840
Thanks.

211
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:45,080
Sending a message to a year later,

212
00:11:45,270 --> 00:11:46,480
that’s quite meaningful.

213
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:47,600
Do you want to try it?

214
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:52,440
Sure. Then I'll give you a love letter.

215
00:11:54,710 --> 00:11:55,670
(Time-travel phone booth)

216
00:11:55,670 --> 00:11:57,480
Rock, paper, scissors.

217
00:12:00,630 --> 00:12:01,440
You go first.

218
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:09,700
(Time-travel phone booth)

219
00:12:22,630 --> 00:12:24,630
I've already guessed

220
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:27,240
that when you receive this postcard

221
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,360
and hear this recording,

222
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:32,870
you'll scold me.

223
00:12:34,050 --> 00:12:35,770
You'll scold me for not keeping my word,

224
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:37,790
for being selfish,

225
00:12:39,390 --> 00:12:40,870
for leaving you alone again.

226
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:42,510
You might even add,

227
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,120
"Men's promises are lies."

228
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:46,870
Am I right?

229
00:12:47,630 --> 00:12:50,670
Suddenly,
I don't know how to address you.

230
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,670
Hello, Wei Ziqi.

231
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:58,080
I am your girlfriend, Yuan Xia.

232
00:12:58,550 --> 00:13:00,000
The Wei Ziqi I'm calling

233
00:13:00,630 --> 00:13:03,630
is the one listening to
this recording now;

234
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:07,790
the one who brings me
an umbrella on rainy days,

235
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:09,720
(Time-travel phone booth)
cooks for me,

236
00:13:10,270 --> 00:13:12,200
goes to the farmers' market with me,

237
00:13:12,510 --> 00:13:16,600
and spends each day with me.

238
00:13:16,960 --> 00:13:18,600
Actually, I never told you

239
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:21,670
how grateful I am
that we are still together

240
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:24,720
after learning about my fate
in another timeline.

241
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:27,790
I'm grateful for
all the beautiful memories we have.

242
00:13:28,390 --> 00:13:29,630
However, slowly,

243
00:13:30,150 --> 00:13:32,030
this gratitude turned into fear

244
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,120
because we've had such beautiful pasts,

245
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:38,480
and I'm afraid of the pain of losing it.

246
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:40,600
I can't imagine

247
00:13:41,510 --> 00:13:43,120
how another timeline's Wei Ziqi

248
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:47,630
endured the time after losing you.

249
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:50,030
I don't know if,

250
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:52,670
when you hear this recording,

251
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:56,320
I am still by your side.

252
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:57,510
If I am,

253
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:01,550
I think you'll be moved to tears

254
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:03,790
when listening to this recording.

255
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,670
You'll rush over to me,

256
00:14:05,670 --> 00:14:08,200
hug me, and kiss me.

257
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,030
Yuan Xia.

258
00:14:13,630 --> 00:14:14,910
In my life,

259
00:14:15,870 --> 00:14:17,440
there have been two turning points.

260
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:18,360
(Time-travel phone booth)

261
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:20,080
The first was the death of my parents.

262
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:24,080
It destroyed all the beauty in my life.

263
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,120
The other is you.

264
00:14:26,910 --> 00:14:28,440
You broke into that attic,

265
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:31,240
bringing your unique vitality.

266
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,910
At that moment, I suddenly felt

267
00:14:34,340 --> 00:14:36,480
that blooming flowers
aren't the most beautiful season;

268
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,390
this moment is.

269
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:42,440
I unconsciously became a thief,

270
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:44,240
hiding you in this chaotic time

271
00:14:44,630 --> 00:14:47,000
which I should have been cleaning up

272
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:49,960
all by myself.

273
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:52,440
I don't know
if we've gotten married by then,

274
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:56,200
but I think you love me so much

275
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:59,030
that you must have proposed
to me by now.

276
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:03,000
If not,

277
00:15:03,790 --> 00:15:06,080
let me tell you in advance.

278
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:11,240
Wei Ziqi,

279
00:15:15,790 --> 00:15:17,030
